---
description: Author integration tests that exercise real boundaries (DB, HTTP, queue)
alwaysApply: false
---

# Write integration tests

- Exercise contracts between modules: HTTP, database, queue, filesystem, third-party SDK.
- Use ephemeral environments (containers, fixtures, transactions) over shared state.
- Reset state between tests; never rely on test order.
- Assert observable behavior, not internal call counts.
- Stub only what you can't run locally (paid APIs, hardware); contract-test those separately.
- Keep wall time reasonable; group slow ones behind a marker / tag.
